hopobject.body: I've got a full-time job globalpillzmart.com Energy-performance assessors are keen on promoting the more expensive “intelligent” night-storage heaters. These are not really intelligent at all, of course, but they do have thermostats that can control the off-peak charging rate, which takes some of the guesswork out of where to set the input dial during those changeable spring and autumn periods. I have two of these in my home – one Dimplex and one Creda – and they both work well.
